1. Install python: sudo apt-get install python3.6
2. Create blog folder
3. Move to blog folder and install virtual environment with: sudo apt-get install python3.6-venv
4. Create venv environment: python3.6 -m venv venv
5. Install flask: sudo pip install flask
6. Install Pymongo dependencies: sudo apt-get install build-essential python-dev
7. Install MongoDb: sudo apt-get install -y mongodb-org
8. Install pymongo: sudo python3.6 -m pip install pymongo
9. Initialize mongo service: mongod

To run the application:
1. Initialize the MongoDB service in a console with the command: mongod
3. In another console, inside the blog folder, activate the venv environment: source venv/bin/activate
3. Run the flask application: python app.py
4. Enter your localhost from the browser!

